Individual Name Popularities

Eugene Miller

I used the string Eugene to search for my name, as this is the only spelling of my name I am aware of. My name seems to be the most popular name that starts with letters Eug as the popularity of names that start with Eug and Eugene track very closely to each other.

My name has become less popular since I was born, and its popularity continues to decline every year. In 1980 the popularity was 6.932510^{-4} in my birth year 1999: 2.369610^{-4} and in 2018: 7.22611110^{-5}.

Emily Archambault

The regular expression I used to match the various spellings of my name is ^E[m]+[ai][l]+[iey]+$. The popularity of my name in 2018 is 0.002766, compared to when I was born in 2001 which was 0.0138412, a difference of 0.01107516. The popularity of all (female) names starting with Emi in 2018 is 0.0040707, which is 0.001304714 greater than the proportion of my name alone.

I search my name by finding the string Katherine directly. I found that the popularity of name Katherine in 2018 is 7.644766710^{-4} and the popularity of it in 1998 which is the year that I was born is 0.0042332. From the differences of number, it seems like Katherine used to be a popular name but less popular at present. And the popularity of Kat in 2018 is 0.002573, compared to 1998 which is 0.0171367, this name is much less popular than it used to be.

Johnny Tamanaha

The regular expression I used for my name was ^Jo[ah]?[n]+ie[y]*$. There has been a small steady decline of Johnnys since my birth year. Other names that start with Joh have been on a heavy decline from 1880 to 2018, so my name has become relatively more popular in comparison to those names.

kaiyuan Fan

I use Frank to be regular expression to find my name in dataset. The popularity of my name in 1998 is 9.293910^{-4}. However, the popularity of my name in 2018 is 2.30260610^{-4}. Obviously, the popularity declined over years which shows on the plot above. The popularity of all (male) names starting with Fra in 2018 is 2018, 0.0011688, which is 0.001168795. It is greater than the proportion of my name alone.
